The '''Australian Beverages Council''', previously known as the '''Australian Soft Drinks Association''' ('''ASDA''')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://australianbeverages.org/lib/pdf/MR160804AustBev.pdf |title=Australian Beverages Council – new name for ASDA |date=17 August 2004 |work=Australian Beverages |accessdate=2009-03-26 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070831054632/http://australianbeverages.org/lib/pdf/MR160804AustBev.pdf |archivedate=2007-08-31 |df= }}</ref> is an industry group that represents the interests of Australian manufacturers, importers and distributors of non-alcoholic beverages. Their headquarters is in [[Waterloo, New South Wales|Waterloo]], [[New South Wales]], [[Australia]].
