{{Redirect|BEc|other uses|Bec (disambiguation){{!}}Bec|and|BEC (disambiguation){{!}}BEC}} {{Globalize|article|Australia|date=December 2017}} The '''Bachelor of Economics''' (BEc or BEcon) is a four-year [[academic degree]] in the [[social science]]s encompassing both qualitative and [[Mathematical model|quantitative]] courses. Typical mandatory courses for the degree include [[microeconomics]], [[macroeconomics]], [[econometrics]], [[economic statistics]], [[history of economic thought]] and [[political economy]].
Some [[university|universities]] offer [[undergraduate degree]] students the opportunity to specialise in a particular area of economics, such as: [[agricultural economics]], [[econometrics]], environmental and resource economics, [[financial economics]], and [[political economy]].<ref name="University of Sydney course information">{{cite web|url=http://sydney.edu.au/courses/bachelor-of-economics|title=BACHELOR OF ECONOMICS|publisher=The University of Sydney}}</ref>
==By country== In Australia, a '''Bachelor of Economics with Honours''' degree is a four-year degree and is taken subsequently as an extension to the three-year Bachelor of Economics. The degree consists of a single-year full-time program. The degree requires more academic courses with a researched [[thesis]] component.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://sydney.edu.au/courses/courses/uc/bachelor-of-economics-honours.html |title=Bachelor of Economics (Honours) |website=University of Sydney |access-date=2018-10-17}}</ref>
In Hong Kong, the [[University of Hong Kong]] offers a four-year Bachelor of Economics degree,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fbe.hku.hk/academic-programmes/undergraduate/becon |title=Bachelor of Economics [BEcon] |website=University of Hong Kong |access-date=2018-10-17}}</ref> with an option to take a double major in Economics and Finance.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fbe.hku.hk/academic-programmes/undergraduate/becon-fin |title=Bachelor of Economics and Finance [BEcon&Fin] |website=University of Hong Kong |access-date=2018-10-17}}</ref>
==See also== *[[Economics education]] *[[Outline of economics]] *[[Philosophy, Politics and Economics|Philosophy, Politics and Economics degree]] *[[Schools of economic thought]]
