{{Infobox football biography | name = Edwin Cubero | image = | fullname = Edwin Cubero Rivera | height = | birth_date = {{birth date|1924|02|11}} | birth_place = [[Belén (canton)|San Antonio de Belén]], [[Costa Rica]] | death_date = {{death date and age|2000|03|08|1924|02|11}} | death_place = [[Guadalajara, Jalisco|Guadalajara]], [[Mexico]] | currentclub = | clubnumber = | position = [[Striker (association football)|Striker]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = | years2 = | years3 = 1948 | years4 = 1948–1954 | years5 = 1954–1955 | clubs1 = [[C.S. Herediano|Herediano]] | clubs2 = Juan Bosco | clubs3 = Sport Club La Libertad | clubs4 = [[Club Atlas|Atlas]] | clubs5 = [[Puebla F.C.|Puebla]] | caps1 = | caps2 = | caps3 = 3 | caps4 = | caps5 = | goals1 = | goals2 = | goals3 = | goals4 = 81 | goals5 = | nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = | pcupdate = }}
{{spanish name 2|Cubero|Rivera}} ''' Edwin Cubero Rivera''' (11 February 1924 - 8 March 2000) was a [[Costa Rica]]n professional [[association football|footballer]] who played for several clubs in Costa Rica and Mexico, enjoying his greatest success with [[Club Atlas|Atlas]].<ref>[http://www.magazinemx.com/bj/articulos/articulos.php?art=3275 Edwin Cubero, el tico que dio un titulo]</ref>
==Club career== Born in [[Belén (canton)|San Antonio de Belén]],<ref name="Bio" /> Cubero is the all-time leading goalscorer for Atlas and was an important part of the club during the 1950-51 season, their only championship-winning season.<ref>[http://www.atlas.naranya.com/noticias_oficiales.php?nota_id=39 Atlas :: Historia por años]</ref> He joined [[Puebla F.C.|Puebla]] after Atlas released him.<ref>[http://wvw.nacion.com/ln_ee/2000/marzo/20/deportes25.html Héroe en casa ajena Edwin Cubero, el máximo artillero histórico del Atlas mexicano] - Nación {{es|icon}}</ref>
==Later life and death== After retiring as a player, Cubero founded the Mudanzas Cubero moving company.<ref name="Bio">[http://www.mudanzascubero.com/Web/Historia.aspx Historia] - Mudanzas Cubero {{es|icon}}</ref>
In March 2000, Cubero died from renal failure in Guadalajara, [[Mexico]].<ref>[https://archive.is/20020104151647/http://www.terra.com.mx/deportes/nota/20000308/096308.htm MUERE COSTARRICENSE CUBERO QUE DIO A ATLAS ÚNICO TÍTULO]</ref>
