{{Infobox football biography | name = Vladyslav Helzin | image = Vladyslav Helzin 1.jpg | fullname = Vladyslav Hryhorovych Helzin | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1973|08|27}} | birth_place = [[Donetsk]], [[Ukrainian SSR]] | height = {{height|m=1.80|precision=0}} | currentclub = [[FC Olimpik Donetsk|Olimpik Donetsk]] (president) | clubnumber = | position = [[Striker (association football)|Striker]] | youthyears1 = 1987 | youthclubs1 = [[FC Shakhtar Donetsk|Shakhtar Donetsk]] | years1 = 2000 | years2 = 2004–2016 | years3 = 2018 | clubs1 = [[FC Mashynobudivnyk Druzhkivka|Mashynobudivnyk Druzhkivka]] | clubs2 = [[FC Olimpik Donetsk|Olimpik Donetsk]] | clubs3 = [[FC Olimpik Donetsk|Olimpik Donetsk]] | caps1 = 0 | caps2 = 144 | caps3 = 0 | goals1 = 0 | goals2 = 24 | goals3 = 0 | nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = | manageryears1 = 1999–2001 | managerclubs1 = [[FC Metalurh Donetsk|Metalurh Donetsk]] <small>''(vice-president)''</small> | manageryears2 = 2001– | managerclubs2 = [[FC Olimpik Donetsk|Olimpik Donetsk]] <small>''(president)''</small> | pcupdate = 11 May 2018 | ntupdate = }}
'''Vladyslav Helzin''' ({{lang-ua|Владислав Григорович Гельзін}}; born 27 August 1973 in [[Donetsk]], [[Ukrainian SSR]]) is a [[Ukraine|Ukrainian]] public figure, politician, footballer and football functionary, president of [[FC Olimpik Donetsk]]. In various media his last name also spells through Russian transliteration as ''Gelzin''. On 10 May 2016, Helzin officially retired from professional sport.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20160510141356/http://www.ua-football.com/ukrainian/high/1462886479-gelzin-zavershil-kareru.html Helzin ended career]. [[UA-Football]]. 10 May 2016</ref>
==Career== He is the only president out of all [[Ukrainian Premier League|premier league]] football clubs in Ukraine, who was also a field team player. Helzin is a [[professional]] [[football (association)|football]] [[Striker (association football)|striker]] who played for the [[Ukrainian Premier League]] club [[FC Olimpik Donetsk]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=footboom.com|script-title=ru:Владислав Гельзин: "Альтман говорил: ты или играй, или бизнесом занимайся"|url=http://www.footboom.com/ukrainian/first/18-12-2013-Vladislav-Gelzin-Altman-govoril-ty-ili-igray-ili-biznesom-zanimajsja.html|language=Russian|date=2014-05-21}}</ref> Additionally he is a deputy of Donetsk Regional Council and a member of the [[Party of Regions]].
Helzin graduated from [[National University of Physical Education and Sport of Ukraine|Donetsk State Institute of Health, Physical Education and Sport]], in "Olympic and professional sports" and [[Donetsk National University]], in "International Economics".
From 1999 to 2001 he served as a vice-President of [[FC Metalurh Donetsk]]. Since 2001 and currently he is a President of the Foundation in development of football in the Donetsk region "Olimpik".
He is married and has two daughters.
